place.name: CAENBY
place.gazetteerText: CAENBY, a parish in the district and county of Lincoln; 6½ miles NW of Wickenby r. station, and 7 W of Market-Rasen. Post Town, Glentham, under Market-Rasen. Acres, 1,430. Real property, £2,413. Pop., 125. Houses, 25. The manor and property belong to SirM. L. Monck, Bart. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £304.* Patron, SirM. L. Monck, Bart. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
